# Salesforce Security Guidelines

## Data Security
- Never expose sensitive data in client-side code
- Use appropriate access modifiers for methods and properties
- Implement proper data validation and sanitization
- Follow the principle of least privilege

## Authentication & Authorization
- Implement proper session management
- Use appropriate authentication mechanisms
- Validate user permissions before performing operations
- Never store sensitive credentials in code

## Input Validation
- Validate all user inputs
- Implement proper escaping for HTML/JS content
- Use strong type checking
- Implement proper error handling for invalid inputs

## XSS Prevention
- Use Lightning Data Service for data operations
- Avoid using innerHTML
- Properly escape all dynamic content
- Use platform security features

## CRUD/FLS
- Respect Field-Level Security
- Implement proper CRUD checks
- Use with sharing where appropriate
- Validate access permissions

## API Security
- Use named credentials for external services
- Implement proper API versioning
- Use appropriate authentication for API calls
- Validate API responses

## Error Handling
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Never expose internal error details to users
- Log security-relevant events
- Handle errors gracefully

